<br>
1) Melees. Now that their unbuffed HP is so high and their resists are high enough to partially resist any normal DD, there really is no reason for the 66% nerf.<br>
<br>
2) Healers. A druid/shaman with chloroblast can out-heal lure spells with chloroblast and at half the mana cost and a lower cast time. Obviously Clerics with Remedy are even worse and I won't even get into Torpor (thank god for golem wands / egg shaped pumice to dispell it). With resist gear, Draughts won't do full damage anyway, and since there is no simple solution to 66% heals in PvP, the damage nerf really does need to be removed.<br>
<br>
I think back in the item loot days when casters ran around wielding only a Slime Crystal Staff and a Stein of Moggok and melees only wielding weapons and no armor, it was balanced. Spells almost always landed for full, root and stun were viable possibilities and made the Wizard class much more well-rounded in PvP. Because most nukes landed for full because few people wore resist gear for fear of it being taken from them if they die, reducing spell damage to 66% damage just helped to even the playing field a bit. But now it just isn't needed anymore.<br>
<br>
-Toth <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujeshuah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeshuah</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/9/01 6:01:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Whats the purpose of the 66% nerf</span><hr size=1> leave 66% penalty.<br>
